The paper deals with generating facial expressions and affect recognition, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks for affect recognition, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of lab-controlled and in-the-wild databases, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
